WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:12.186 --> 00:13.553
What is that,
three in a row?

00:13.937 --> 00:15.838
That would be four,
actually.

00:15.905 --> 00:17.206
- Oh, God.
- Come on.

00:17.273 --> 00:18.607
What do you say,
we go five outta nine?

00:18.675 --> 00:20.709
So you can keep abusing me?
No, thank you.

00:20.777 --> 00:21.939
- I'm done.
- Oh, come on.

00:22.006 --> 00:23.302
I'll spot you three.

00:23.370 --> 00:24.619
Game time's over, Wyatt.
They're here.

00:24.687 --> 00:25.859
They're here?

00:25.927 --> 00:27.322
You can set up
in the conference room.

00:27.390 --> 00:28.691
Yeah.
No, I'm just...

00:28.759 --> 00:32.756
Get set up in
the conference room.

00:32.824 --> 00:35.056
- You did let him win, right?
- It wasn't easy.

00:35.124 --> 00:36.990
The guy has the coordination
of a two-year-old.

00:37.058 --> 00:39.490
I know, the last time these
venture capitalists came in,

00:39.557 --> 00:41.025
I took him boxing to
calm him down.

00:41.092 --> 00:43.225
I basically had to punch myself
in the face to let him win.

00:45.060 --> 00:46.894
I don't get it.
I mean, if he's such a genius,

00:46.962 --> 00:48.832
why does he get so nervous
around a bunch of investors?

00:48.899 --> 00:50.870
Eh, you spend
two years working on

00:50.937 --> 00:52.338
a satellite phone
that fits in your pocket

00:52.405 --> 00:53.606
and then bet
the company on it.

00:53.674 --> 00:55.411
You'd be a little
nervous too, I think.

00:55.479 --> 00:57.280
The prototype...

00:57.348 --> 00:59.216
I can't find it.
I don't know where I--

00:59.284 --> 01:01.187
You mean this?

01:01.255 --> 01:02.591
I don't know
what I'd do without you.

01:02.658 --> 01:05.093
- Fail miserably.
- I would.

01:05.161 --> 01:07.799
- Is that the...
- $20 million prototype, yes.

01:07.867 --> 01:09.435
And you don't even
get to look at this bad boy

01:09.502 --> 01:11.204
until after
we close the deal today.

01:11.271 --> 01:13.441
Wow, they're
like storm troopers.

01:13.509 --> 01:15.943
Storm troopers
don't write checks.

01:16.011 --> 01:17.813
Now all you gotta do
is walk in there,

01:17.881 --> 01:19.281
show them
how the phone works...

01:19.349 --> 01:22.487
Right, and Suntech Digital
will be a new force

01:22.554 --> 01:24.656
in global communications.
Let's knock 'em dead.

01:26.759 --> 01:29.396
All right.

01:29.463 --> 01:30.965
Wait, wait.
Where do you think you're going?

01:31.032 --> 01:32.967
Into the room
with the people.

01:33.034 --> 01:35.538
Wrong, that's
the adult table in there.

01:35.605 --> 01:37.273
And you haven't
earned the privilege yet.

01:37.341 --> 01:38.742
But I played
air hockey with him--

01:38.810 --> 01:39.977
You need to
go back to the office

01:40.045 --> 01:41.345
and file
a patent for the phone.

01:41.413 --> 01:43.347
A patent? I don't
know how to file a patent.

01:43.415 --> 01:45.182
- Figure it out.
- Can't we do that after--

01:45.250 --> 01:47.184
No, and you keep talking,
I'm gonna start billing you.

01:47.252 --> 01:48.886
And my time
runs $1,000 an hour.

01:48.953 --> 01:50.854
But isn't this our time,
Mr. Hand?

01:52.991 --> 01:54.425
I stand corrected.

01:54.493 --> 01:56.127
<i>Your Fast Times</i>
<i>at Ridgemont High</i> quote,

01:56.194 --> 01:58.862
that proves you
belong at the adult table.

01:58.930 --> 02:01.198
Hey,
that's a great movie.

02:01.265 --> 02:02.932
And it spoke
to a generation...

02:13.480 --> 02:16.349
Hey, you busy?

02:19.987 --> 02:22.156
Okay, have you
ever filed a patent before?

02:22.224 --> 02:23.724
I just got back from
this meeting with Harvey

02:23.792 --> 02:25.092
and he wants me
to file this patent,

02:25.160 --> 02:27.027
but I have no idea what
that paperwork looks like.

02:27.095 --> 02:29.964
So...any help in
this arena would be re--

02:32.300 --> 02:33.734
Did Harvey call you
and tell you to do that?

02:43.410 --> 02:45.544
If it isn't the golden boy.

02:45.612 --> 02:47.680
You're Harvey's
project, right?

02:47.748 --> 02:50.250
What's your name?
Mike, Mike Ross.

02:50.318 --> 02:51.685
Gregory Boone.

02:51.753 --> 02:53.387
So what are you doing here?

02:53.455 --> 02:56.424
Weren't you signing some big
deal this afternoon downtown?

02:56.492 --> 02:58.594
Well, evidently I haven't
earned the privilege yet.

02:58.661 --> 02:59.862
Get the adult table speech?

03:03.300 --> 03:05.000
Yeah, instead of
watching the deal close,

03:05.068 --> 03:07.003
I get to file the patent.

03:07.070 --> 03:08.904
Yeah, those suck.

03:10.707 --> 03:13.242
Wait, you--you've done
one of these before?

03:13.310 --> 03:15.411
Like 100.
Why?

03:20.250 --> 03:21.950
Uh, uh, uh, uh.

03:23.786 --> 03:25.353
Now.

03:25.421 --> 03:27.289
It's okay,
you don't have to apologize.

03:27.356 --> 03:29.057
I took care of it.

03:29.125 --> 03:30.593
Patent claim.

03:30.660 --> 03:32.161
I negotiated a deal
to get it done.

03:32.229 --> 03:33.429
What are you talking about?

03:33.497 --> 03:35.599
Gregory.
He agreed to file it for me.

03:35.666 --> 03:37.701
And all I have to do is
proof his Bainbridge briefs.

03:37.768 --> 03:40.504
Ah. That explains
why he said to give you this.

03:42.941 --> 03:44.542
And why he called you a sucker.

03:46.311 --> 03:47.445
He called me a what now?

03:49.982 --> 03:54.386
Mike Ross, allow me to
introduce the Bainbridge briefs.

03:54.454 --> 03:57.757
- Which stack?
- All of them.

03:57.824 --> 03:59.192
Wait a minute,
are these all--

03:59.259 --> 04:01.194
Still printing, yeah.
I'd give it about a half hour.

04:01.262 --> 04:05.132
Um...that's six printers,
23 pages a minute, 30 minutes.

04:05.199 --> 04:08.836
That's 4,140 pages.
Plus all this.

04:08.903 --> 04:10.905
Which means the next time
you negotiate a deal,

04:10.972 --> 04:12.740
I would suggest
to get your facts straight.

04:12.808 --> 04:15.410
Uh...
I am a sucker.

04:15.478 --> 04:17.779
Mm-hmm.

04:17.846 --> 04:20.015
When did that happen?

04:20.082 --> 04:21.583
[Ima Robot's <i>Greenback Boogie</i>

04:21.651 --> 04:23.818
♪ See the money wanna stay
for your meal ♪

04:23.886 --> 04:27.322
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

04:27.389 --> 04:30.959
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feels ♪

04:31.027 --> 04:34.063
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

04:34.130 --> 04:37.099
♪ living in a beehive,
of your mind ♪

04:37.167 --> 04:41.170
♪ me and Mrs.
busy, busy making money ♪

04:41.238 --> 04:42.471
♪ all right ♪

04:42.539 --> 04:44.194
♪ yes, hey, hey,
♪

